---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Github, Linkedin } from '@phosphor-icons/react';
---

<Layout 
  title="Silent Commit - Software Development Insights"
  description="A developer's thoughts on software engineering, coding practices, and technology insights. Featuring posts on React, TypeScript, and modern web development."
  keywords="software development, coding, programming, react, typescript, web development, engineering, tech blog"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center px-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center space-y-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1 class="text-6xl font-light tracking-tight text-foreground">
            Silent Commit
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
            A developer's thoughts on software engineering, coding practices, and technology insights
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-8 pt-8">
          <a 
            href="/posts" 
            class="px-8 py-3 bg-foreground text-background rounded transition-colors hover:bg-muted-foreground"
          >
            Read Posts
          </a>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <a 
              href="https://github.com/Franciscuo" 
              target="_blank" 
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
              aria-label="GitHub Profile"
            >
              <Github size={24} />
            </a>
            <a 
              href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/franciscuo/" 
              target="_blank" 
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
              aria-label="LinkedIn Profile"
            >
              <Linkedin size={24} />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="py-24 px-8 border-t border-border">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-light mb-8 text-foreground">About</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-foreground leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Welcome to Silent Commit, where I share insights from my journey in software development. 
            This blog focuses on practical knowledge gained from building and maintaining systems in production.
          </p>
          <p>
            You'll find posts about system architecture, React patterns, TypeScript best practices, 
            and lessons learned from real-world projects. Each post aims to provide actionable insights 
            that you can apply to your own development work.
          </p>
          <p>
            I believe in sharing knowledge openly and helping other developers navigate the complexities 
            of modern software development. Whether you're debugging production issues, designing scalable 
            systems, or optimizing performance, there's something here for you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Recent Posts Preview -->
    <section class="py-24 px-8 border-t border-border">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-light text-foreground">Latest Posts</h2>
          <a 
            href="/posts" 
            class="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
          >
            View all →
          </a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <!-- These will be populated by Astro's static generation -->
          <article class="group">
            <a href="/posts/building-resilient-systems" class="block space-y-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground group-hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">
                Building Resilient Systems: Lessons from Production
              </h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                After years of building and maintaining systems in production, I've learned that resilience isn't just about handling errors—it's about designing systems that gracefully degrade and recover from unexpected failures.
              </p>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <time>January 15, 2024</time>
                <span>•</span>
                <span>8 min read</span>
              </div>
            </a>
          </article>
          
          <article class="group">
            <a href="/posts/typescript-patterns-real-world" class="block space-y-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground group-hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">
                TypeScript Patterns That Actually Matter in Real Projects
              </h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                TypeScript has transformed how we write JavaScript, but not all patterns are created equal. Here are the patterns that consistently add value without unnecessary complexity.
              </p>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <time>January 20, 2024</time>
                <span>•</span>
                <span>6 min read</span>
              </div>
            </a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    background-color: oklch(0.06 0 0);
    color: oklch(0.93 0 0);
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  
  .font-mono {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  }
</style>